Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.redis.client

Interface ArrayResultHandler

public interface ArrayResultHandler
Handler for Redis commands that return an array.

Arrays contain a list of RESP values which may be bulk strings, integers, nested arrays, or null values.

Commands returning arrays:

  • KEYS - list of matching keys
  • LRANGE - list of elements
  • SMEMBERS - set members
  • HGETALL - alternating field/value pairs
  • MGET - values for multiple keys (may include nulls)
  • EXEC - transaction results
  • ZRANGE - sorted set members
  • SCAN - cursor and array of keys
Author:
Chris Burdess

  • Method Details

    • handleResult

      void handleResult(List<RESPValue> array, RedisSession session)
      Called when the command succeeds with an array result.

      The array contains RESPValue objects which can be queried for their type and converted to appropriate Java types.

      Processing example:

      
 void handleResult(List<RESPValue> array, RedisSession session) {
     for (RESPValue value : array) {
         if (value.isNull()) {
             // Handle null
         } else if (value.isBulkString()) {
             byte[] data = value.asBytes();
         } else if (value.isInteger()) {
             long num = value.asLong();
         }
     }
 }
      Parameters:
      array - the array elements
      session - the session for further operations
